subSubSection.paragraph:
Solanum triflorum Type. Belgium. Antwerpen, 14 Oct 1984,
J.-E. De Langhe & R. D'hose s.n. [219/84
] (holotype: "in herbario De Langhe sub numero 219/84", not seen, BR?).

(Figure 
54
). Native to the Americas with an amphitropical distribution between temperate South and North America. Introduced outside its native range in Europe, South Africa and Australia, probably with agricultural seed or wool waste.

Australia: cut-leaf nightshade (
Walsh and Entwisle 1999
), three-flowered nightshade (
Harden 1993
); United Kingdom: small nightshade (
Stace 2010
).
